annotationA: XRCC1 protein; Damaged DNA binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: nucleotide-excision repair; cellular response to DNA damage stimulus; lateral inhibition; base-excision repair, AP site formation; single strand break repair
annotationB: Aprataxin and PNK-like factor; Displays apurinic-apyrimidinic (AP) endonuclease and 3'- 5' exonuclease activities in vitro
